## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="975f5-105">В следующей таблице перечислены параметры, принятые этим атрибутом, а также сведения о том, какой аспект конфигурации поставщика позволяет контролировать.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-105">The following table lists the parameters accepted by this attribute along with what aspect of the provider configuration it enables you to control.</span></span>  
  
|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-106">Параметр</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-106">Parameter</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-107">Настраивает</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-107">Configures</span></span>|  
|---------------|----------------|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.Scope>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-108">Пространство имен, в котором поставщик предоставляет классы.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-108">The namespace in which your provider exposes classes.</span></span>|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.NamespaceSecurity>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-109">— Безопасность (DACL) для используемого пространства имен.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-109">-   The security (DACL) on the namespace used.</span></span>|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.HostingModel>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-110">— Модель размещения, которая будет использоваться поставщиком.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-110">-   The hosting model that will be used by the provider.</span></span>|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.IdentifyLevel>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-111">— Режим олицетворения поставщика.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-111">-   The impersonation mode of the provider.</span></span>|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.HostingGroup>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-112">Группа размещения, к которой принадлежит поставщик.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-112">The hosting group that the provider belongs to.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="975f5-113">Этот параметр применяется только к внутрипроцессного поставщикам.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-113">This parameter only applies to in-process providers.</span></span>|  
|<xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.WmiConfigurationAttribute.SecurityRestriction>|<span data-ttu-id="975f5-114">Безопасность (DACL) для поставщика WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="975f5-114">The security (DACL) on the WMI provider.</span></span>|  
  
   
  
## Examples  
  
```  
// Specify that this assembly contains code that implements a WMI  
// Provider. Use the assembly:WmiConfiguration attribute to define  
// the WMI namespace, the hosting model, and the impersonation mode  
// of the WMI provider.  
// The attribute below specifies that the class this provider  
// exposes to WMI will be in the root/MortgageCalc namespace, will  
// use the decoupled hosting model and will not allow the provider  
// to impersonate its callers.  
  
[assembly: WmiConfiguration("root/MortgageCalc",HostingModel = ManagementHostingModel.Decoupled, IdentifyLevel = false)]  
```
